solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int smallestValue(int n) {
        while (true) {
            int sum = 0, x = n;
            for (int p = 2; p * p <= x; ++p) {
                while (x % p == 0) {
                    sum += p;
                    x /= p;
                }
            }
            if (x > 1) sum += x;
            if (sum == n) return n;
            n = sum;
        }
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly factor n into its prime factors (with multiplicity) and replace n by their sum until the sum equals n, which is the fixed point and the smallest value. The loop terminates quickly because the sum of prime factors is usually much smaller than n.

